## Core SDK Concepts

### `query()` — The Main Entry Point

```typescript
import { query } from "@anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk";

for await (const message of query({
  prompt: "Process this invoice and extract line items",
  options: {
    model: "sonnet",                        // or "opus", "haiku"
    allowedTools: ["Read", "Bash", "Glob"], // whitelist tools
    permissionMode: "bypassPermissions",    // auto-approve in sandboxed envs
    maxTurns: 50,                           // cap runaway loops
    systemPrompt: "You are a document processing agent...",
    mcpServers: [customToolServer],         // your custom tools
  }
})) {
  // Each iteration yields: reasoning, tool call, tool result, or final outcome
}
```

`query()` creates a fresh session each call — no memory of previous interactions. You manage conversation continuity externally (database, session resumption).

### `ClaudeSDKClient` — For Long-Running Interactive Sessions

Provides a class instance with methods for session management. Better for long-running applications where you need fine-grained lifecycle control. Supports bidirectional conversations, custom tools via hooks, and streaming.

### Built-In Tools

Read, Write, Edit, MultiEdit, Bash, Glob, Grep, WebSearch, WebFetch, Agent (subagents), NotebookEdit, AskUserQuestion. These are the same tools Claude Code uses internally.

### Custom Tools (In-Process MCP Servers)

Register your own domain-specific tools alongside built-in ones. Custom tools run as in-process MCP servers — no separate processes needed.

```typescript
import { tool, createSdkMcpServer } from "@anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk";

const crmServer = createSdkMcpServer({
  name: "my-crm",
  version: "1.0.0",
  tools: [
    tool("update_contact", "Update a CRM contact record", {
      contact_id: "string",
      fields: "object"
    }, async (args) => {
      const result = await supabase.from('contacts').update(args.fields)
        .eq('id', args.contact_id);
      return { content: [{ type: "text", text: JSON.stringify(result) }] };
    }),
    tool("log_activity", "Log an agent activity", {
      type: "string",
      description: "string"
    }, async (args) => {
      // ... write to activity log
      return { content: [{ type: "text", text: "Activity logged" }] };
    })
  ]
});

// Pass to query options
options: { mcpServers: [crmServer] }
```

### Permissions & Security Hooks

```typescript
options: {
  permissionMode: "bypassPermissions", // use in sandboxed envs only
  canUseTool: async (toolName, input) => {
    // Intercept and control tool execution
    if (toolName === "Bash" && input.command?.includes("rm -rf")) {
      return { behavior: "deny", message: "Destructive commands blocked" };
    }
    if (toolName === "Write" && input.file_path?.includes(".env")) {
      return { behavior: "deny", message: "Cannot modify env files" };
    }
    return { behavior: "allow", updatedInput: input };
  }
}
```

### Structured Output

```typescript
const reviewSchema = {
  type: "object",
  properties: {
    issues: { type: "array", items: { /* ... */ } },
    summary: { type: "string" },
    score: { type: "number" }
  },
  required: ["issues", "summary", "score"]
};

options: {
  outputFormat: { type: "json_schema", schema: reviewSchema }
}
```

### Skills & CLAUDE.md

The SDK supports Claude Code's filesystem-based configuration (skills, CLAUDE.md, hooks) but loads nothing by default. Opt in explicitly:

```typescript
options: {
  settingSources: ["user", "project"],  // load from ~/.claude/ and ./.claude/
  allowedTools: ["Skill", "Read", "Write", "Bash"]
}
```

### System Prompt Control

```typescript
// Option 1: Custom system prompt (recommended for SaaS)
options: { systemPrompt: "You are a freight document reconciliation agent..." }

// Option 2: Use Claude Code's default system prompt
options: { systemPrompt: { type: "preset", preset: "claude_code" } }
```

