## Cost Model

### Token Costs (Dominant)
The primary cost driver. A typical agentic session uses significantly more tokens than a single API call because the agent loop involves multiple rounds of reasoning + tool calls + tool results.

### Sandbox Compute Costs
- Vercel: $0.128/active CPU hour (I/O wait excluded)
- Fly.io Sprites: $0.07/CPU-hour, $0.04375/GB-hour
- E2B: Usage-based, varies by plan
- State storage on Vercel: free

### Example Math
100 users × 20 messages/day × 30 seconds average compute per message:
- Active CPU time: ~16.7 hours/day = ~$2.13/day in sandbox costs
- Token costs will be 10-50x this depending on model and turn count

### Cost Controls
- `maxTurns` — cap loop iterations
- `maxBudgetUsd` — hard budget limit per query
- Use Haiku for simple tasks, Sonnet for complex ones
- Use snapshots to eliminate repeated setup costs (npm install, etc.)

