## When to Use What — Decision Framework

### Use Raw API (Vercel AI SDK + Anthropic provider)
- Stateless chat interactions (WhatsApp bots, customer support)
- Simple tool calling with typed tools you define
- Provider-agnostic requirement (want to swap models)
- No filesystem access needed
- **→ This is Sunder's current architecture. It's the right choice.**

### Use Agent SDK
- Agent needs to read/write/execute in a filesystem
- Complex multi-step document processing (RedDoc's reconciliation pipeline)
- Need Claude Code's built-in file editing, bash, context compaction
- Building a coding assistant or code generation platform
- Willing to lock into Claude as provider

### Use CLI Shell-Out
- CI/CD pipelines, automated code reviews
- One-shot tasks where you just want a result
- Dev-time scripting
- Don't need programmatic mid-execution control

